name: PushCase
auth_description: Requires a user of type `Api` with functionality `PushCases:None`

headers.name: EVA-User-Agent
headers.description: The user agent that is making these calls. Don't make this specific per device/browser but per application. This should be of the form: `MyFirstUserAgent/1.0.0`

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnitID
headers.description: The ID of the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnit-Query
headers.description: The query that selects the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-IDs-Mode
headers.description: The IDs mode to run this request in. Currently only `ExternalIDs` is supported.

headers.name: EVA-IDs-BackendSystemID
headers.description: The ID of the backend system that is used to resolve the IDs.

C.name: ID
C.description: This is the ID of a `User`

C.name: Remove
C.description: If specified as true, the assignee will be removed from the case.

E.name: Delete
E.description: If specified as true, the item will be deleted.

E.name: OrderLineID
E.description: This is the ID of a `OrderLine`

E.name: ProductID
E.description: This is the ID of a `Product`

D.name: OrderID
D.description: This is the ID of a `Order`

F.name: Name
F.description: Required if pushing and creating a previously non-existent CaseTopic

F.name: ParentBackendID
F.description: Provide a ParentID, or nothing if the CaseTopic should be root-level.

G.name: AccountType
G.description:
Is this a Standard/Basic/Incognito account?
Possible values:

* `0` - Standard
* `1` - Basic
* `2` - Incognito

G.name: CountryID
G.description:
ISO 3166-1

This is the ID of a `Country`

This string must be between 2 (incl) and 2 (incl) characters long.

G.name: Gender
G.description: Possible values are: M, F, O

G.name: LanguageID
G.description:
ISO 639-1

This is the ID of a `Language`

J.name: Delete
J.description: If specified as true, the interaction will be deleted.

J.name: Type
J.description:
Possible values:

* `0` - Communication
* `0` - PublicNote
* `1` - Note
* `1` - PrivateNote
* `2` - Ledger
* `3` - Email

B.name: AssignedOrganizationUnitBackendID
B.description: OU the case is assigned to. When set this will influence visibility.

B.name: CaseTopic
B.description:
The topic that this case is a part of. If a BackendID is provided and a CaseTopic exists with that ID, that CaseTopic is used, no matter what Name or ParentBackendID are passed and if they match.
  If no CaseTopic exists with the given BackendID, but one does exist with the given Name and ParentBackendID, that CaseTopic is used instead, disregarding what BackendID was passed in the request.
  If none of these conditions are met, a new CaseTopic is created.

**Required since 756:** Field CaseTopic is required and will be enforced as such in 2.0.788.

**Will be enforced in 772**

B.name: Customer
B.description: Providing a `null` value and not providing the property at all has different meanings.

B.name: DisableEventExports
B.description: Setting this to true will try to suppress as many event exports as possible that might result from this call.

B.name: ID
B.description:
The ID field can be used to update an existing Case (specifically to be able to update the backend ID). If the ID is provided, the Update field does not need to be set.

This is the ID of a `Case`

B.name: Priority
B.description:
Possible values:

* `0` - Low
* `1` - Medium
* `2` - High
* `9` - Critical

B.name: Title
B.description: This string must be between 1 (incl) and 255 (incl) characters long.

B.name: Topic
B.deprecation_notice:
**Deprecated since 756:** Topic is deprecated and will be removed in 2.0.788: The topic should now be passed into CaseTopic.

**Will be removed in 772**
B.description:
**Deprecated since 756:** Topic is deprecated and will be removed in 2.0.788: The topic should now be passed into CaseTopic.

**Will be removed in 772**

B.name: Update
B.description: Setting this to true will update the case information if it already exists instead of throwing an error.

L.name: Code
L.description: A unique ID identifying this error.

L.name: Message
L.description: A human-readable message describing the error.

L.name: RequestID
L.description: A unique ID identifying the request. Please provide this ID when contacting support.

L.name: Type
L.description: A short description of the error type.

M.name: ExternalIDs
M.description: When using the `ExternalIDs` mode, this will hold the resolved external IDs.

M.name: IsAsyncResultAvailable
M.description: This is a flag indicating whether the async request is done. If it is `null`, it is not an async service. If it is `false`, the response is not yet available. Do not process the properties in that case. It is is `true` the properties are filled with the result of the call.

M.name: UnresolvedExternalIDs
M.description: When using the `ExternalIDs` mode, this will hold the external IDs we couldn't resolve.

K.name: ID
K.description: This is the ID of a `Case`
